DTSTART:20260307T150000Z
DTEND:20260307T180000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T000000Z
SUMMARY:MIFI HOTSPOTS!
DESCRIPTION:Do you or someone you know need internet access at home?\n\nThe 
 City of Durham and Durham County have launched a new program to provide 
 free internet access to qualifying residents through MiFi hotspot 
 distribution. Visit the website to complete the survey to see if you 
 qualify!\n\nEmail the Digital Inclusion Services Team for any questions or 
 additional information at digitalinclusion@durhamnc.gov \n\n\n\nClick here 
 to access the Survey in English and Spanish\n\nResidents may pick up their 
 devices during one of the following distribution windows in the Main 
 Library MakerLab located on the first floor. \n\nThis project is a 
 collaboration with the City and County of Durham. Applications will remain 
 open until November 2025 or when funds are depleted. MiFi program 
 recipients will begin receiving devices in September 2025.\n\nQualifying 
 Documents Information\n\n\n	One survey per household\n	Must be at least 18 
 years of age to apply\n\n\nMiFi qualifications include either income 
 limitations or income-based government assistance. Applicants must be able 
 to provide photo identification and proof of eligibility by emailing 
 qualifying document(s) to digitalinclusion@durhamnc.gov  or bringing a copy 
 of qualifying document(s) at pick up.\n\nThe following forms of 
 identification are accepted:\n\n\n	Current Driver's License\n	Current State 
 Issued Identification Card\n	Current Passport\n	Military 
 Identification\n\n\nNet Income Accepted Documents Include\n\n\n	Prior 
 year’s state\, federal\, or tribal tax return (W2 forms or pay stubs NOT 
 accepted)\n	Social Security statement of benefits\n	Veteran Administration 
 statement of benefits\n	Retirement/pension statement of 
 benefits\n	Unemployment Compensation statement of benefits\n	Federal or 
 tribal notice letter of participation in General 
 Assistance\n\n\nIncome-Based Government Assistance Accepted Documents 
 Include\n\n\n	Food support (SNAP)\n	Employment services\n	Extended Foster 
 Care\n	Head Start\n	Home Energy Assistance Program (LIHEAP)\n	Medicaid or 
 Medical Assistance\n	Free or Reduced Lunch Program\n	Section 8\, Federal 
 Public Housing\n	Social Security Disability\n	Supplemental Security 
 Income\n	Statement of benefits from Social Security\, General Assistance\, 
 Veteran Administration\n	Retirement/Pension or Unemployment 
 Benefits\n\n\n\n\nNeed additional information? Call 919-560-9311
LOCATION:MakerLab\, Main Library (300 N. Roxboro St)
ORGANIZER;CN="Megan Koslofsky":MAILTO:mkoslofsky@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Computer Class, Digital/Tech Literacy, Durham
UID:LibCal-14288-16486669
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/16486669
END:VEVENT
