SUMMARY:Multi-Sensory Environment Open House
DESCRIPTION:Check out Main Library's Multi-Sensory Environment! Drop in\, 
 try out the equipment\, and learn more about what our sensory space 
 offers.\n\nThe Multi Sensory Environment provides immersive\, interactive 
 experiences through sight\, sound\, touch\, and smell. The room can be used 
 for play\, therapy\, or teaching\, and sound and light are adjustable to 
 meet visitor needs. All ages welcome!\n\n(The Multi-Sensory Environment is 
 located on the 4th Floor at Main Library.)
LOCATION:Multi Sensory Environment\, Main Library (300 N. Roxboro St)
ORGANIZER;CN="Jennifer Jamsky":MAILTO:jjamsky@dconc.gov
