SUMMARY:Flexible Book Club
DESCRIPTION:Join our community book club! Whether or not you've had a 
 chance to read the book\, we welcome everyone to participate. Our 
 discussion questions are broad\, so anyone can join the conversation. We 
 explore a wide range of genres—from historical fiction and romance to 
 mystery and non-fiction—ensuring there's something for everyone. The 
 Flexible Book Club is a fantastic way to connect with fellow book lovers in 
 the Durham community and share your passion for reading!\n\nThe selection 
 for this month is A Woman of No Importance by Sonia Purnell.\n\nEmail 
 cruth@dconc.gov or call 919-560-8648 for more information.
LOCATION:Southwest Meeting Room\, Southwest Regional Library (3605 Shannon Rd)
ORGANIZER;CN="Carmen Ruth":MAILTO:cruth@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Book Club
