SUMMARY:The Secret to Smoother Days: What Your Family's Behavior is Really Telling You with Emerge Pediatric Therapy
DESCRIPTION:Durham County Library is excited to partner with Emerge 
 Pediatric Therapy to provide this FREE parenting workshop! \n\nThis 
 workshop\, hosted by Brittni Winslow of Emerge\, will provide parents 
 with:\n\n\n	Practical strategies to reduce chaos\n	Improvement for daily 
 transitions\n	Tools to identify & accommodate different sensory 
 needs\n\n\nRegistration is required. Please only register adults who are 
 attending\; children are welcome to join their caregivers but do not need 
 to be registered.\n\nIf you have any accessibility questions or 
 accommodation needs\, please contact us at 
 Accessibility_Services@dconc.gov. We ask that all requests be made at least 
 three (3) business days prior to the event to ensure we can provide the 
 best accommodations possible!
LOCATION:Southwest Regional - Children's Programming Room\, Southwest Regional Library (3605 Shannon Rd)
ORGANIZER;CN="Accessibility Services":MAILTO:accessibility_services@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Accommodations Available, Classes & Lectures, Community Engagement
