SUMMARY:*POSTPONED* Using Data to Build your Business
DESCRIPTION:\na {\n    text-decoration: none\;\n    color: #464feb\;\n}\ntr 
 th\, tr td {\n    border: 1px solid #e6e6e6\;\n}\ntr th {\n    
 background-color: #f5f5f5\;\n}\n\nHave a great business idea but need solid 
 data to back it up? Join us for a hands-on workshop where we’ll guide you 
 step-by-step through the library’s powerful business databases and 
 research tools. Learn how to find market trends\, analyze competitors\, and 
 gather data that supports your business plan. Perfect for entrepreneurs and 
 small business owners ready to make informed decisions. Whether you’re 
 launching a startup or growing an existing business\, this workshop will 
 give you the blueprint you need to succeed.\n\nThis workshop repeats on May 
 11.\n\n
LOCATION:Computer Lab\, Main Library (300 N. Roxboro St)
ORGANIZER;CN="Jana Bradley":MAILTO:jbradley@dconc.gov
