SUMMARY:CANCELLED - The GPA Game: From Application to Acceptance
DESCRIPTION:9th\, 10th\, and 11th grade families — are you ready for the 
 college admissions process?\n\nJoin us for The GPA Game: From Application 
 to Acceptance\n\nThis free\, one-hour seminar will help students stand out 
 in the college admissions process while giving parents peace of mind about 
 costs and next steps. Through an engaging\, interactive activity\, families 
 will discover practical strategies to maximize opportunities\, learn ways 
 to reduce stress during the admissions journey\, and gain the confidence to 
 move successfully from application to acceptance.  This seminar will be 
 presented by A2Z College Planning.  Registration is recommended and 
 appreciated.\n\n
LOCATION:East Meeting Room\, East Regional Library (211 Lick Creek Lane)
ORGANIZER;CN="Archie B.":MAILTO:pburke@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Career Development
