SUMMARY:Indie Lens Pop-Up Screening: The Inquisitor
DESCRIPTION:Eventbrite registration link\n\nIn Partnership with PBS North 
 Carolina we invite you to:\n\n\n\nIndie Lens Pop-Up Screening: The 
 Inquisitor\nTuesday\, March 10 | 6:00-8:30 PM\nDurham County Main 
 Library\n300 N Roxboro Street\, Durham\n\nEventbrite registration link\n\n 
 \n\n \n\n\n\nJoin us for a special screening and discussion of THE 
 INQUISITOR\, a new Independent Lens documentary chronicling the life and 
 legacy of Barbara Jordan—her role in shaping American democracy\, her 
 leadership during moments like Nixon’s impeachment\, and the personal 
 challenges she faced behind the scenes.\n\n\n\nThe screening will be 
 followed by a community conversation and Q&A with local leaders and 
 subject-matter experts\, reflecting on Barbara Jordan’s impact\, women in 
 public service\, and women leaders making change in our community 
 today.\n\n\n\nEventbrite registration link\n\nWatch The Inquisitor 
 Trailer\n\n\n\n\nWhere can I park when the Main Library parking lot is 
 full?\n\nParking is available in the library parking lot or at the North 
 Queen Street Garage located at 115 North Queen Street which is behind the 
 apartments directly across the street from the library. Parking is free in 
 the garage. Please bring your ticket to a service desk in the library for 
 validation.\n\n
LOCATION:Main Auditorium\, Main Library (300 N. Roxboro St)
ORGANIZER;CN="Celeste Holtzmann":MAILTO:choltzmann@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Humanities, Movie
UID:LibCal-14288-16390861
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/16390861
END:VEVENT
