BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260311T220000Z
DTEND:20260311T230000Z
DTSTAMP:20260311T000000Z
SUMMARY:Genre of the Month Book Club
DESCRIPTION:12 months\, 12 genres\, 12 chances to broaden your reading 
 horizons!\n\n \n\nWelcome to the Genre of the Month Book Club! Each month\, 
 we explore a different (sub)genre\, and you choose to read any book that 
 fits that theme--no assigned reading here! Then\, join us on the second 
 Wednesday of every month at Boxyard RTP. Grab yourself a drink or snack as 
 we discuss what we read and the genre as a whole.\n\n \n\nThe book club 
 meets outside\, so dress for the weather! Our table is located next to RTP 
 Uncorked and the elevator\, near the dog park. If you've found a table 
 reserved for book club\, you're in the right place!\n\n\n\n \n\nClick on 
 one of the months below to see what our members chose to read!\n\n 
 \n\nJanuary: Self Help\n\nFebruary: Romantasy\n\nMarch: Satire\n\nApril: 
 Poetry\n\nMay: Cozy Mystery\n\nJune: Epistolary\n\nJuly: 
 Cyberpunk\n\nAugust: Coming of Age/Bildungsroman\n\nSeptember: Banned 
 Classic \n\nOctober: Gothic Horror\n\nNovember: History\n\nDecember: Short 
 Story Collection/Anthology\n\n \n\nQuestions? Email Elle at 
 kfarmer@dconc.gov.\n\n \n\nBoxyard RTP\n\n900 Park Offices\n\nResearch 
 Triangle Park\, NC 27709\n
LOCATION:Offsite
ORGANIZER;CN="Elle F.":MAILTO:kfarmer@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Book Club
UID:LibCal-14288-15686749
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/15686749
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260311T220000Z
DTEND:20260311T230000Z
DTSTAMP:20260311T000000Z
SUMMARY:Real Estate Essentials
DESCRIPTION:Real estate is one of the most powerful tools for building 
 long-term wealth and financial stability. This educational workshop will 
 explore how owning property can help you build equity\, generate passive 
 income\, and create generational wealth. Whether you're a first-time buyer 
 or looking to invest\, you'll gain practical insights into navigating the 
 real estate market with confidence. Join us to learn how to turn property 
 ownership into a pathway to financial freedom. Presented by licensed real 
 estate agent Larry Thomas.
LOCATION:Conference Room #3214\, Main Library (300 N. Roxboro St)
ORGANIZER;CN="Austin Daniels":MAILTO:ausdaniels@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Business, Finance
UID:LibCal-14288-16259121
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/16259121
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260311T220000Z
DTEND:20260311T233000Z
DTSTAMP:20260311T000000Z
SUMMARY:Wednesday Computer Class @ Main
DESCRIPTION:Come join a supportive group environment for self-paced digital 
 skills courses. We'll be using Northstar Digital Literacy\, a free online 
 resource available to all Durham County Library patrons. A library staff 
 member will be present to get you set up and answer questions as each 
 participant moves through online modules on their own at their own pace. 
 Northstar allows you to track your learning progress and earn badges or 
 certificates for completing a course. These classes are best for learners 
 who have at least basic keyboard and mouse skills. Our computer lab has a 
 limited number of laptops for use\, so bringing your own laptop and 
 headphones is encouraged.\n\nComputer and digital skills topics 
 include:\n\n\n	Phone Keyboard Basics & Logging In\n	Basic Computer 
 Skills\n	Internet Basics\n	Using Email\n	Windows 10 & 11\n	Mac 
 OS\n	Microsoft Word\, Excel\, and PowerPoint\n	Google Docs\n	Social 
 Media\n	Information Literacy\n	Career Search Skills\n	Your Digital 
 Footprint\n	Accessing Telehealth Appointments\n	Cybersecurity 
 Basics\n\n\nThese classes are self-paced and each week participants will 
 choose which lessons they want to complete on their own. You do not need to 
 have come to the first class to attend the following weeks and there is no 
 requirement to commit to all of the classes through April. Register for the 
 weeks that work best for you!\n\nIf you have any questions or accommodation 
 needs\, contact Jimmy McKinnell at jmckinnell@dconc.gov or call 
 919-560-9940
LOCATION:Computer Lab\, Main Library (300 N. Roxboro St)
ORGANIZER;CN="James McKinnell":MAILTO:jmckinnell@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Computer Class, Digital/Tech Literacy
UID:LibCal-14288-16276908
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/16276908
END:VEVENT
