SUMMARY:Memory Cafe
DESCRIPTION:Come join us for a monthly activity for people with dementia 
 and their caregivers. Memory Cafes host activities designed to engage in 
 the present\, without the expectations of using short-term memory or 
 forward thinking. This month\, we will make bird feeders. Even if you can't 
 name the birds anymore\, watching them is a stimulating activity anyone can 
 participate in. So join us to make some feeders. \n\nIf you have any 
 accessibility questions or accommodation needs\, please contact me at 
 dpeterson@dconc.gov. We ask that all requests be made at least three (3) 
 business days prior to the event to ensure we can provide the best 
 accommodations possible! Please email me if you plan to attend and have nut 
 allergies so that we can make accommodations.
LOCATION:North Regional - Children's Programming Room\, North Regional Library (221 Milton Rd)
ORGANIZER;CN="Desiree Peterson":MAILTO:dpeterson@dconc.gov
