SUMMARY:Canines for Literacy @ East
DESCRIPTION:Relax and read with a dog! This program brings dogs and 
 reluctant readers together for 20 minutes of companionship. Handlers and 
 their dogs provide quiet encouragement to children so that they might 
 develop a love of reading and  improve communication skills. Canines for 
 Literacy is an affiliate program of Reading Education Assistance Dogs® 
 (R.E.A.D.®).\n\nRegistration is required. Please note that you may book 
 one session per day\, and sessions are 20 minutes long. Available time 
 slots are as follows: 2:00pm\, 2:20 pm\, 2:40pm. \n\nIf it's less than 24 
 hrs before the event\, give us a call and see if we have any avaialbe time 
 slots left!\n\nBow Wow for now!\n\n
LOCATION:East Regional - Children's Programming Room\, East Regional Library (211 Lick Creek Lane)
