SUMMARY:Accepting Submissions: Poetry on Display
DESCRIPTION:Submit your poetry to be featured in the East Regional 
 Library's National Poetry Month display!\n\nChildren\, Teens\, and Adults 
 are invited to submit up to two poems to be displayed. Community poems will 
 be displayed throughout the library from April 2026-April 
 2027.\n\nGuidelines:\n\n\n	Poems must be submitted by Friday\, March 27\, 
 2026 \n	Up to two poems per person will be accepted \n	Please include your 
 name on your submission\, unless you'd like to remain anonymous\n	Kindly 
 keep each poem limited to one page\n	Please keep your submissions family 
 friendly\; the library will not display adult themes or poetry using adult 
 language\n\n\nQuestions and completed poems can be emailed to Mara 
 Plantholt at: mplantholt@dconc.gov
LOCATION:East Regional Library (211 Lick Creek Lane)
ORGANIZER;CN="Mara Plantholt":MAILTO:mplantholt@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Writing
