SUMMARY:Heartfulness Meditation
DESCRIPTION:Heartfulness meditation practice is a simple and effective way 
 to integrate meditation into our daily lives. The Heartfulness technique 
 shows us how to gently turn our attention toward our hearts and experience 
 that inner presence for ourselves. There will be a brief introduction and 
 instruction\, followed by a guided relaxation\, leading into a silent 
 heart-centered meditation. Sessions are conducted by a certified 
 Heartfulness meditation instructor and open to everyone over the age of 15. 
 No prior experience necessary. Registration is not required.\n\nIf you have 
 questions about accessibility\, program stimulation levels\, and/or need 
 disability accommodations\, please contact us at 919-560-7192.
LOCATION:Southwest Regional - Children's Programming Room\, Southwest Regional Library (3605 Shannon Rd)
ORGANIZER;CN="Carmen Ruth":MAILTO:cruth@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Health & Fitness, Low Sensory Stimulation
