SUMMARY:**POSTPONED** - Home Repair Lab Special Edition: How to Fix a Leak
DESCRIPTION:This program has now been rescheduled! Please note the new date 
 and time here - https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/16594000 
 Please re-register for your spot. Thank you!\n\nThis program will not occur 
 tonight due to incoming severe weather. We will send out the rescheduled 
 date once we have it confirmed. Please stay safe at home tonight! \n\nJoin 
 Chris and Mindy Meyers from Home Repair Lab for an exclusive class at their 
 shop! This class will include lecture information\, followed by some 
 hands-on practice and Q&A.\n\nIn this month's program\, we'll be joined by 
 staff with the City of Durham Water Department for a special program for 
 Fix a Leak Week! City of Durham staff will kick off the program\, then 
 participants will learn how to fix basic leaks with Chris and Mindy. 
 Relevant for homeowners\, first time home buyers\, and renters. 
 Registration is required\, and participants will sign a safety waiver for 
 Home Repair Lab. Home Repair Lab is located at 803 Ramseur St Suite E\, 
 Durham\, NC 27701.\n\nNote: This program is a repeat of content from last 
 year\, so if you attend last year\, you will not need to attend 
 again.\n\n*Special note: This program is offsite and the building is not 
 ADA-complient. If you have any accessibility questions or accommodation 
 needs\, please contact us at Maker_STEAM@dconc.gov. We ask that all 
 requests be made at least 3 business days prior to the event to ensure we 
 can provide the best accommodations possible!
LOCATION:Offsite
ORGANIZER;CN="Caroline Flory":MAILTO:cflory@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Maker, STEAM
