SUMMARY:RESCHEDULED Connected Currents: A Creek Week Panel Discussion on Upstream and Downstream Water Quality
DESCRIPTION:Once a new date has been determined a new event listing will be 
 posted. \n\n \n\nConnected Currents: A Creek Week Panel Discussion on 
 Upstream and Downstream Water Quality \n\nWater connects us all—flowing 
 across communities\, industries\, and ecosystems. But what happens upstream 
 doesn’t always stay upstream. Join a distinguished panel of water 
 professionals as they explore the relationship between upstream and 
 downstream activities and water quality and the ways different 
 organizations and individuals are involved. \n\n  \n\nThis engaging 
 discussion will bring together experts in stormwater engineering\, PFAS 
 (per- and polyfluoroalkyl substances or “forever chemicals”)\, 
 watersheds\, pollution\, sedimentation\, and more to examine how human 
 impacts influence waterways from headwaters to receiving waters. Panelists 
 will share their professional experience\, research\, solutions\, and 
 collaborative strategies that protect water quality across entire 
 watersheds! \n\n  \n\nPanelists include:  \n\nDr. Colleen Brown- UNCW 
 \n\nEmily Sutton- Haw River Assembly \n\nRachylle Hart- NC PFAS Testing 
 Network \n\nMcKenzie Bradshaw\, PE\, CFM- Durham County Stormwater \n\n  
 \n\nCreek Week provides opportunities for Durham residents to discover and 
 explore local streams and lakes through educational programs and 
 recreational activities and to do their part to protect waterways through 
 volunteer projects. Learn more About Creek Week at Keep Durham Beautiful 
 \n\n\n\nMarch 16 starting at 6 pm in the Main Library auditorium located at 
 300 North Roxboro Street in Durham. \n\nParking is available in the library 
 parking lot or at the North Queen Street Garage located at 115 North Queen 
 Street which is behind the apartments directly across the street from the 
 library. Parking at the garage is free. Please bring your parking ticket to 
 a service point for validation.     \n\nRegistration is appreciated to 
 receive an email reminder\, cancellation link\, and program updates. 
 Seating is first come first served. Registration does not hold or guarantee 
 a seat.   \n\nQuestions? Email mkoslofsky@dconc.gov
LOCATION:Main Auditorium\, Main Library (300 N. Roxboro St)
ORGANIZER;CN="Megan Koslofsky":MAILTO:mkoslofsky@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Classes & Lectures, Durham, Environmental, Gardening, Health & Fitness, STEAM
UID:LibCal-14288-16275986
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/16275986
END:VEVENT
