SUMMARY:Matter of Balance
DESCRIPTION:A Matter of Balance is an award-winning program designed to 
 reduce the fear of falling and increase activity levels among older adults. 
 This 8-class series will show participants exercises to help improve 
 balance and prevent the likelihood of future falls. This event is 
 co-sponsored by Duke Trauma Center and the Durham Center for Senior 
 Life.\n\nRegistration is required. Registering for a session will register 
 you for all sessions.\n\nIf you have any questions or accommodation needs\, 
 please contact Raivynn at 919-560-0147 or raivynnsmith@dconc.gov. We ask 
 that all accessibility requests be made at least three (3) business days 
 prior to the event to ensure we can provide the best accommodations 
 possible!\n
LOCATION:Southwest Meeting Room\, Southwest Regional Library (3605 Shannon Rd)
ORGANIZER;CN="Raivynn Smith":MAILTO:raivynnsmith@dconc.gov
