BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260318T163000Z
DTEND:20260318T180000Z
DTSTAMP:20260318T000000Z
SUMMARY:Testers & Tasters Cookbook Club
DESCRIPTION:\n\nTesters & Tasters Cookbook Club is a place to talk about 
 food and cooking!\n\nCome share your experiments\, experiences\, triumphs\, 
 and tragedies.\n\nThis month's theme: Newspaper Recipes!\n\nIf you're old 
 enough to remember when the newspaper was delivered to your house every 
 morning\, or lucky enough to have inherited your mom or grandma's recipe 
 collection\, odds are good that you already have some recipes that were 
 clipped from a newspaper. But that's not the only way to find a newspaper 
 recipe. Here are some others:\n\nUse a recipe from a cookbook that was 
 published by a newspaper. The New York Times has many cookbooks (several 
 are on reserve at the Information desk)\, and so do many others. You can 
 find cookbooks from The Oregonian and the Los Angeles Times and others with 
 a free account at The Internet Archive.\n\nLook up "recipes" with the name 
 of a newspaper. Even newspapers that require a paid subscription to read 
 them online sometimes have a free recipe site. Here's the News & Observer's 
 recipe page. For the Herald-Sun\, you can see old issues by going to the 
 "online resources" section of the library website\, selecting "Magazines 
 and Newspapers\," and searching for the H-S by name. \n\nThere are some 
 cookbooks you can browse through at the Information Desk at North Regional 
 Library\, as well as some food sections from the News and Observer. The 
 books need to stay in the library (staff will make copies of recipes for 
 you) but you can take one of the N&O sections if you see a recipe you 
 like.\n\nWhen you know the name of the dish you'll be bringing\, please 
 email the name and source to etobias@dconc.gov.\n\nAnd don't forget some 
 containers for leftovers!\n\nQuestions? Email etobias@dconc.gov or call 
 919-560-0140.\n\nRegistration closes 24 hours before the meeting\, but 
 email me if you've missed the deadline and still want to come.\n\nHappy 
 Cooking to all!\n\n \n\nAll in-person programming is subject to change or 
 cancellation based on current COVID conditions.\n\n
LOCATION:North Meeting Room - Full Room\, North Regional Library (221 Milton Rd)
ORGANIZER;CN="Emily Tobias":MAILTO:etobias@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Book Club, Food & Cooking
UID:LibCal-14288-15946877
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/15946877
END:VEVENT
