SUMMARY:SCORE presents: Introduction to Recordkeeping
DESCRIPTION:YOU MUST REGISTER VIA SCORE'S LINK\n\n \n\nSCORE Chapel Hill 
 Durham is excited to introduce a workshop for new entrepreneurs or anyone 
 else in need of learning simple record keeping. This course is a hands-on 
 lecture/lab that teaches business owners how to track their cash 
 disbursements and receipts in a simple manner to keep track of 
 profitability on a consistent basis.\n\nThe workshop requires each student 
 to bring their own laptop computer to the classroom\, and have Microsoft 
 Excel loaded onto the computer and functioning properly. A basic 
 understanding of how to use Excel and enter information into a spreadsheet 
 is required to attend. \n\nThe workshop will be taught by Ms.Camille 
 Blommer\, a certified instructor for SCORE\, and CPA who holds a Masters in 
 Accountancy..\n\nMs. Blommer will email you the two MS Excel 
 templates/schedules that you will need to have for the class. Students must 
 register via the SCORE link provided at least two days before the class to 
 enable Ms. Blommer time to send you the two schedules and have time to 
 download onto your own laptop computer. There is no fee for the 
 class.\n\nSeating is limited —maximum attendees will be 15.
LOCATION:Meeting Room #4347\, Main Library (300 N. Roxboro St)
ORGANIZER;CN="Jana Bradley":MAILTO:jbradley@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Business, Career Development, Finance, Low Sensory Stimulation
UID:LibCal-14288-15430656
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/15430656
END:VEVENT
