SUMMARY:Page & Pen Writing Workshop
DESCRIPTION:\n\nGrab your notebook and a pen\, and let's write! The Page & 
 Pen Writing Workshop meets every six weeks and is open to anyone who wants 
 to improve their creative writing skills. Session formats vary and may 
 include writing exercises\, discussion about technique and process\, 
 sharing ideas for organizing work sessions and workspaces\, or exploration 
 of any challenges you may be facing in the struggle to write.\n\nTopic for 
 this session: Planning and Structure\n\nDo you create an outline before you 
 write? Do you start madly typing without a plan and then see where it all 
 leads? Do you structure your poems ahead-of-time? If you're planning a 
 novel\, do you know how it ends before you start? Nonfiction writers: do 
 you identify a goal before you begin your work?\n\nThere are countless ways 
 to approach the planning of any writing project. Let's see how many of them 
 we can investigate during our one-hour session.\n\nClick here for a library 
 book list on planning and structure.\n\n\n\nThis program is open to anyone 
 at any time: drop in once\, attend every session\, or show up every once in 
 a while -- no long-term commitment is required. Space is often limited\, so 
 please register in advance.\n\nContact Bob with any questions: 
 rskesler@dconc.gov
LOCATION:North Meeting Room - Full Room\, North Regional Library (221 Milton Rd)
ORGANIZER;CN="Bob S.":MAILTO:rskesler@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Writing
UID:LibCal-14288-15825062
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/15825062
END:VEVENT
