SUMMARY:Board Game Cafe
DESCRIPTION:Want to try out a new board game? Are you looking to play some 
 classics\, but you're not sure how to find other players to join you? Then 
 come grab a warm beverage\, pick out a game\, and meet others in your 
 community at our Board Game Cafe!\n\nThe Board Game Cafe will provide 
 community members with some warming drinks and a variety of board games to 
 play in the library. The board games 
 include:\n\n\n	Cartographers\n	Codenames\n	Dominion\n	Mysterium\n	One Night 
 Ultimate Werewolf\n	Really Loud Librarians\n	Scrabble\n	Settlers of 
 Catan\n	Splendor\n	Sushi Go\n	Ticket to Ride\n	Trivial 
 Pursuit\n	Uno\n	Villainous\n	Wingspan\n	Yeti In My Spaghetti\n	& 
 more!\n\n\nCommunity members are also welcome to bring snacks and their own 
 favorite board games to share at the event.\n\nRegistration is appreciated 
 but not required.\n\nQuestions? Contact Mara (she/her): 
 mplantholt@dconc.gov.
LOCATION:East Meeting Room\, East Regional Library (211 Lick Creek Lane)
ORGANIZER;CN="Mara Plantholt":MAILTO:mplantholt@dconc.gov
