BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260323T220000Z
DTEND:20260323T230000Z
DTSTAMP:20260323T000000Z
SUMMARY:Adult Story Time -- Irish Fairy Tales
DESCRIPTION:Read-alouds are for grown-ups too! Join us for a weekday 
 evening adult story time at the North Regional Library. Flop on the carpet 
 with a floor pillow\, pull up a chair\, or sit at a table if you want to 
 bring your own dinner or snacks. Spend an hour listening to read-alouds 
 from books and stories in the library collection. Tea\, coffee\, and hot 
 chocolate will be provided.\n\nThis month: Irish Fairy Tales.\n\nThe 
 eternal cycles of birth and death\, pleasure and pain\, love and loss\, and 
 reality and fantasy\, have always been at the heart of Irish mythology. 
 Here fairies and demons walk hand in hand with mortals\, and anything can 
 happen. These tales from a collection by Jeremiah Curtin are sometimes 
 frightening\, usually insightful\, and always entertaining.\n\nRegistration 
 is appreciated but not required.\n\nE-mail Bob with any questions: 
 rskesler@dconc.gov
LOCATION:North Meeting Room - Full Room\, North Regional Library (221 Milton Rd)
ORGANIZER;CN="Bob S.":MAILTO:rskesler@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Story Time
UID:LibCal-14288-16071712
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/16071712
END:VEVENT
