SUMMARY:Storytime @ The Hub Farm
DESCRIPTION:Please join us for a spring-themed storytime at the beautiful 
 Hub Farm!  \n\nThe Hub Farm is a 30-acre outdoor learning center located at 
 117 Milton Road\, Durham\, NC 27712 (adjacent to North Regional Library). 
 For more information\, please visit their website at 
 https://www.thehubfarm.org/. \n\nDirections: From downtown Durham take 
 Roxboro Road north to the stoplight at Milton Road. Turn left and continue 
 past Eno Valley Elementary. Immediately after the school look for signs to 
 the Hub Farm on your left. Parking is available in the Hub Farm Visitor 
 Parking lot\, which is in the Eno Valley Elementary bus lot. \n\nThis 
 storytime will take place outside\, weather permitting. There is a paved 
 path down to the event area\, which is a covered pavilion area. While some 
 seating is available\, we recommend bringing your own blankets or chairs 
 and to wear comfortable clothing. Afterward\, please feel free to stay and 
 explore the farm until 11 a.m.\n\nIf you have any accessibility questions 
 or needs\, please contact Lauren at lwise@dconc.gov. We ask that all 
 requests be made at least three (3) business days prior to the event to 
 ensure we can provide the best accommodations possible!\n\nRegistration for 
 this event is required. There are a total of 45 seats available. When 
 registering\, please remember to include all people in your party. Due to 
 space limitations\, those who are not registered will be unable to attend.  
 \n\nQuestions? Please email Lauren at lwise@dconc.gov.  Thank you!
LOCATION:Offsite
ORGANIZER;CN="Lauren Wise":MAILTO:lwise@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Story Time
