BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260325T220000Z
DTEND:20260325T233000Z
DTSTAMP:20260325T000000Z
SUMMARY:Durham Business Listening Tour
DESCRIPTION:Give It To The People® x Commissioner Michelle Burton x Durham 
 County Library SBC\n\n \n\nAs one of the NC’s leading curators of 
 business education\, professional development\, and ecosystem-building 
 experiences\, Give It To The People® knows that sustainable growth starts 
 with real conversations. This tour is designed to meet business owners 
 where they are\, understand the challenges they face\, and identify how 
 they’re accessing (or struggling to access) the resources available 
 across Durham and the Triangle.\n\nCommissioner Michelle Burton brings the 
 heart of an educator and the vision of a public servant to this initiative. 
 Together\, we are committed to being intentional about listening\, truly 
 listening\, to what Durham’s business community needs to grow\, hire\, 
 scale\, innovate\, and stay competitive.\n\nEvery stop on the tour will 
 create space for entrepreneurs to share their lived experiences\, offer 
 insight on what’s working and what isn’t\, and shape future solutions 
 that reflect the real needs of our community. From new startups to 
 established firms\, from solo consultants to brick-and-mortar owners\, this 
 tour is a chance to ensure Durham’s economic ecosystem is responsive\, 
 equitable\, and built to last.\n\nAs an added benefit\, every attendee will 
 have the opportunity to join the Give It Get It Biz Membership\, the 
 premier hub for small business connectivity\, training\, events\, and 
 ecosystem access in Durham. Membership opens the door to resources\, 
 relationships\, and opportunities that help entrepreneurs navigate the 
 region more effectively and stay plugged into the support system they 
 deserve.\n\nThis Listening Tour is a commitment to building a stronger\, 
 more connected Durham where business owners feel seen\, supported\, and 
 equipped to thrive.\n\nLet’s Give It &  Get It Together.\n\n \n\nREGISTER 
 HERE: Durham Business Listening Tour by Give It To The People
LOCATION:North Meeting Room - Full Room\, North Regional Library (221 Milton Rd)
ORGANIZER;CN="Ciera Williams":MAILTO:cbwilliams@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:
UID:LibCal-14288-15978580
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/15978580
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260325T220000Z
DTEND:20260325T233000Z
DTSTAMP:20260325T000000Z
SUMMARY:Romance Lovers Book Club-A Marvellous Light and Soulless
DESCRIPTION:All things romance!\n\nThis book club talks about all things 
 romance\, starting with the month's theme but quickly branching out into 
 other books we've been reading and loving\, books we want to read\, and 
 what's going on in Romancelandia - you'll walk away every month with lots 
 of recs for your TBR! Because of our wide-ranging discussions\, you should 
 always feel free to drop in even if you haven't gotten a chance to try the 
 book club picks. This month we're reading\, A Marvellous Light by Freya 
 Marske and Soulless by Gail Carriger. If you want to attend this virtual 
 event\, please register or contact Chelsea Romero at cromero@dconc.gov with 
 any questions.
