SUMMARY:Read to a dog @ Southwest!
DESCRIPTION:Relax and read with a dog! This program brings dogs and 
 reluctant readers together for 15 minutes of companionship. Handlers and 
 their dogs provide quiet encouragement to children so that they might 
 develop a love of reading and improve communication skills. Canines for 
 Literacy is an affiliate program of Reading Education Assistance Dogs® 
 (READ®).\n\nPlease note that you may book one session per day\, and 
 sessions are 15 minutes long. Available time slots are as follows\;\n\n4:00 
 pm\, 4:15pm\, 4:30 pm\, and 4:45 pm.\n\nClick here to register for a 
 timeslot via SignUp Genius.\n\n* Note: Please feel free to bring a book or 
 two of your choice to read! When your time slot is about to begin\, please 
 hang out outside the door of the Children's Programming Room and someone 
 will let you in when it is your time to read! Thanks :)\n\nIf you have 
 questions about accessibility\, program stimulation levels\, and/or need 
 disability accommodations\, please contact us at (919) 560-8592.
LOCATION:Southwest Regional - Children's Programming Room\, Southwest Regional Library (3605 Shannon Rd)
ORGANIZER;CN="Abbie Westphalen":MAILTO:awestphalen@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Literacy
UID:LibCal-14288-15314676
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/15314676
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260326T200000Z
DTEND:20260326T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T000000Z
SUMMARY:Technology Thursday: Code Like a Girl
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate Women’s History Month with a fun and inspiring 
 coding adventure! In this hands-on program\, kids will learn about a 
 trailblazing woman in technology—such as Ada Lovelace or Grace 
 Hopper—and discover how her ideas helped shape the digital world we know 
 today. Through storytime and discussion\, children will explore how women 
 have made powerful contributions to computer science and continue to lead 
 the way in innovation. After the story\, participants will jump into action 
 with a beginner-friendly coding tutorial in Scratch\, guided by instructors 
 from Code Wiz. Kids will learn the basics of block-based coding as they 
 create their own simple animation or game. No prior coding experience is 
 needed—just curiosity and creativity!\n\nThis program encourages 
 confidence\, problem-solving\, and big dreams while showing young learners 
 that anyone can code. Join us as we honor women in tech and inspire the 
 next generation of innovators!\n\nIf you have any accessibility questions 
 or accommodation needs\, please contact us at cromero@dconc.gov. We ask 
 that all requests be made at least three (3) business days prior to the 
 event to ensure we can provide the best accommodations possible! All ages 
 are welcome\, but best for ages 8 to 12!
LOCATION:North Meeting Room - Full Room\, North Regional Library (221 Milton Rd)
ORGANIZER;CN="Chelsea Romero":MAILTO:cromero@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:
UID:LibCal-14288-16433473
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/16433473
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260326T201500Z
DTEND:20260326T213000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T000000Z
SUMMARY:Beginner Sewing Machine Tutorial
DESCRIPTION:Join us in Express Yourself for a basic sewing machine 
 tutorial. You will learn the parts of a sewing machine\, how to wind a 
 bobbin\, how to thread the sewing machine\, choose a stitch\, and sew a 
 straight line. This tutorial is designed for absolute beginners. All 
 materials will be provided. Please do not bring your own sewing projects to 
 this tutorial. Questions? Contact Jessica at jllundin@dconc.gov. Open to 
 both adults and teens. \n\nExpress Yourself was made possible through the 
 generosity of the Durham Library Foundation.
LOCATION:Express Yourself / Study Room 3\, South Regional Library (4505 S. Alston Ave)
ORGANIZER;CN="Jessica Lundin":MAILTO:jllundin@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Arts & Crafts, Durham Library Foundation, Express Yourself, Maker, Other
UID:LibCal-14288-16488703
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/16488703
END:VEVENT
