SUMMARY:Book Babies
DESCRIPTION:Please join us for special bonding time with your little one 
 (aged 0-24 months)! At this lapsit-style storytime\, we will spend about 20 
 minutes engaging in structured learning through bounces\, rhymes\, songs\, 
 and books\, followed by 15-45 minutes of unstructured play and 
 socialization time.\n\nNote: A television is used during the first part of 
 the program (about 20 minutes) to display the words to the songs and rhymes 
 (to support adult engagement)\; there are no moving pictures. \n\nOpen for 
 all! If you have any accessibility questions or accommodation needs\, 
 please contact Lauren at lwise@dconc.gov. We ask that all requests be made 
 at least three (3) business days prior to the event to ensure we can 
 provide the best accommodations possible!\n\nThank you to the Durham 
 Library Foundation for their generous support in making this program 
 possible.\n
LOCATION:North Meeting Room - Full Room\, North Regional Library (221 Milton Rd)
ORGANIZER;CN="Lauren Wise":MAILTO:lwise@dconc.gov
