SUMMARY:South TGNBC - Science Fiction Month
DESCRIPTION:Welcome to the South Tween Graphic Novel Book Club 
 (TGNBC)!\n\nEvery month\, the South TGNBC will explore a different genre 
 through reading\, discussion\, a themed snack\, and an activity. \n\nTwo 
 graphic novels will be chosen for each month\, and members can choose to 
 read one or both. Books are available for those who have library cards to 
 pick up at South Regional Library during business hours every day leading 
 up to the meeting. Members must be age 8 - 13 (email amaristorres@dconc.gov 
 to request an exception). An online version may be coming soon\, if there 
 is enough demand.\n\nThe month of March we will be exploring the Science 
 Fiction genre with these graphic novels:\n\n- One Trick Pony by Nathan 
 Hale\n\n- The Postman from Space by Guillaume Perreault\n\n- Bonus: Grace 
 Needs Space by Benjamin A. Wilgus
LOCATION:South Regional - Children's Programming Room\, South Regional Library (4505 S. Alston Ave)
