BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260328T140000Z
DTEND:20260328T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260328T000000Z
SUMMARY:Legal Eagle Community Day & Social Justice Fair
DESCRIPTION:Join the Durham County Library in partnership with NCCU's 
 School of Law\, Legal Aid NC\, Emancipate NC\, and more for a day of free 
 legal resources for the whole community.  An all day resource fair will 
 help attendees connect with programs and resources for their legal needs\, 
 while scheduled panels will provide insight into current legal issues\, 
 including constitutional updates and immigration enforcement.\n\nCheck back 
 here for updates regarding the schedule and programming! Registration is 
 not required\, but register below to receive an email 
 reminder.\n\n**Parking:\n\nPlease be aware that we anticipate a large 
 volume of visitors to the Main Library on this date - Please plan ahead to 
 find parking and allow time to go through the library's security screening 
 process:\n\nParking is available in the library parking lot or at the North 
 Queen Street Garage located at 115 North Queen Street which is behind the 
 apartments directly across the street from the library. Parking at the 
 garage is free. Please bring your parking ticket to a service point for 
 validation.\n\n \n\n \n\nAcompañe a la Biblioteca del Condado de Durham en 
 asociación con la Facultad de Derecho de NCCU\, Legal Aid NC\, Emancipate 
 NC\, y más para un día de recursos legales gratuitos para toda la 
 comunidad.  Una feria de recursos durante todo el día ayudará a los 
 participantes a conectarse con los programas y recursos para sus 
 necesidades legales\, mientras que los paneles programados proporcionarán 
 información sobre temas legales de actualidad\, incluyendo la justicia en 
 la vivienda\, la justicia restaurativa\, y las recientes decisiones de la 
 Corte Suprema.\n\nPor favor\, tenga en cuenta que anticipamos un gran 
 volumen de visitantes a la Biblioteca Principal en esta fecha - Por favor\, 
 planifique con antelación para encontrar aparcamiento\; además del lote 
 libre de la biblioteca\, aparcamiento en la calle está disponible cerca de 
 Queen St.\, y hay un estacionamiento al otro lado de Liberty St. dentro del 
 nuevo edificio de apartamentos.
LOCATION:Main Auditorium\, Main Library (300 N. Roxboro St)
ORGANIZER;CN="Natalie Killion":MAILTO:nkillion@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Career Development, Community Engagement, Finance, Law
UID:LibCal-14288-16407951
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/16407951
END:VEVENT
