SUMMARY:Grow Your Money Tree!
DESCRIPTION:\na {\n    text-decoration: none\;\n    color: #464feb\;\n}\ntr 
 th\, tr td {\n    border: 1px solid #e6e6e6\;\n}\ntr th {\n    
 background-color: #f5f5f5\;\n}\n\n\n\nJoin us for a fun\, hands-on program 
 that teaches kids and families the importance of saving money! Children 
 will create their own money tree craft while learning how small savings can 
 grow over time. Our partners from Self-Help Credit Union will share simple 
 tips for parents to start healthy financial habits at home. This 
 interactive session is perfect for ages 3 and up and includes take-home 
 resources to keep the learning going.
LOCATION:Main Children's Programming Room\, Main Library (300 N. Roxboro St)
ORGANIZER;CN="Austin Daniels":MAILTO:ausdaniels@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Arts & Crafts, Business, Community Engagement, Finance
