SUMMARY:Prostate Cancer Awareness featuring Terry and Tracy Hill
DESCRIPTION:Durham County Library invites you to our community event to 
 learn more about prostate cancer\, early detection\, and what it’s really 
 like to face this disease.\n\nOur featured presenter\, Terry Hill\, will 
 share his powerful journey as a prostate cancer survivor. From diagnosis 
 and treatment to recovery and advocacy. Terry’s story highlights the 
 importance of early screening\, resilience through challenge\, and the 
 impact prostate cancer can have on individuals and families.\n\nTracy 
 Hill\, Terry's wife and partner\, offers a caregiver’s perspective on 
 supporting a loved one through diagnosis\, treatment\, and beyond. Her 
 insights will shed light on the emotional and practical role that 
 caregivers play in the cancer journey.\n\nThis event is open to all who 
 want to learn more about prostate cancer\, including men and families 
 seeking knowledge\, survivors looking for connection\, and community 
 members committed to supporting health education.\n\n📅 Date: Saturday\, 
 March 28\n⏰ Time: 1 PM - 2:30 PM\n📍 Location: South Regional Library\, 
 4505 S. Alston Ave\, Durham NC\, 27713\n\nTogether\, we aim to raise 
 awareness\, reduce stigma\, and empower individuals with life-saving 
 information. Prostate cancer is one of the most common cancers in men\, and 
 early awareness and screening can make a significant difference in 
 outcomes. This event is part of ongoing efforts to promote community 
 education\, support survivors and caregivers\, and encourage proactive 
 health decisions.\n\nFor more information please call: 919-560-8594
LOCATION:South Meeting Room\, South Regional Library (4505 S. Alston Ave)
ORGANIZER;CN="Jason Howard":MAILTO:jchoward@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Health & Fitness
UID:LibCal-14288-16351319
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/16351319
END:VEVENT
