SUMMARY:Plant Swap
DESCRIPTION:Join us for our Spring Plant Swap! It will happen on Saturday\, 
 March 28 from 3:30-4:30 p.m. We’ll have a Master Gardener from Durham 
 County Extension to answer your questions. Drop by to exchange or share 
 houseplants\, vegetable starts\, annuals\, perennials\, or seeds. Please 
 ensure that any items brought in are pest-free and labeled clearly.\n\nSo 
 bring a plant\, take a plant\, check out a gardening book\, or just come 
 and talk to a Master Gardener!\n\nThis is a drop-in event so come anytime 
 during the hour. For more information call 919-560-7192.\n\nIf you have 
 questions about accessibility\, program stimulation levels\, and/or need 
 disability accommodations\, please contact us at 919-560-7192.
LOCATION:Southwest Meeting Room\, Southwest Regional Library (3605 Shannon Rd)
ORGANIZER;CN="Kristen Stockdale":MAILTO:kstockdale@dconc.gov
